Classes

AutoBuilderAttribute

Annotates a builder method that will be invoked to complete the construction of a given dependency.

AutoFactoryAttribute

Annotates a type or constructor that will be invoked to construct a given dependency.

BuilderAttribute

Annotates a builder method that will be invoked to complete the construction of a given dependency.

BuilderReferenceAttribute

Annotates a field or property that references a builder method that will be invoked to complete the construction of a given dependency.

ChildInjectorAttribute

Annotates a method used to retrieve a child injector instance.

DependencyAttribute

Defines an dependency that is required by an injector interface.

FactoryAttribute

Annotates a factory method that will be invoked to construct a given dependency.

FactoryReferenceAttribute

Annotates a field or property that references a factory method that will be invoked to construct a given dependency.

Factory<T>

A type that can be used to inject a dependency on the factory method for a class instead of the class itself.

InjectionUtil

InjectorAttribute

Annotates an injector interface as the entry point to a DAG.

InjectorDependencyAttribute

Annotates an interface as an injector dependency used to pass values from a parent to a child injector.

LabelAttribute

Annotates a factory method or dependency with a unique label used to discriminate them from other dependencies with the same type.

LinkAttribute

Models a link between one dependency key and another.

PartialAttribute

Annotates a factory method as a partial factory. This can be used on a factory that returns a List, Set, or Dictionary to indicate that multiple factories with the same type and qualifiers should be combined into a single dependency.

PhxInjectAttribute

QualifierAttribute

Annotates an attribute as a qualifier that can be applied to a factory method or dependency as a unique label used to discriminate them from other dependencies with the same type.

SpecificationAttribute

Annotates a specification class that contains factory methods and links used to construct a DAG.
